Back in August 2014, the shooting of Michael Brown, an unarmed black teenager, by a white police officer, in Ferguson, Missouri, prompted protests that roiled the area for weeks. In the wake of the controversial police shooting incident, rumors were swirling that the hacktivist collective Anonymous — acting in solidarity with the Black Lives Matter (BLM) movement — had called for ‘Day of Rage’ protests to be staged in cities across the United States on 21 August 2014.
